ial">Re: Faydedar and Inner Fire</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I understand that you didn't have the foresight to make sure nobody else had planned a Faydedar attack, and I would have been willing to forgive and forget had your initial response to my reporting of the situation been at the very least sympathetic. Instead, you came out right on the attack, telling me that the calendar was not a reservation system, are you supposed to check for every spawn in the game before attacking something, etc. Not once did you apologize to me in the course of our conversation, and neither did Rramsa. Neither of you acknowledged that what you did was a terrible inconvenience. Neither of you expressed remorse that Rramsa's actions caused a raid that was planned a week in advance to have to be totally scrapped, and neither of you offered to help kill Faydedar at the next possible spawn time, even when I suggested that would be a possibility and requested such help.<br>
<br>
Had you been the very LEAST bit apologetic, I would be more inclined to feel better about the whole situation. Instead, I received nothing but cold indifference, and I don't like people who mess up my plans and then effectively don't give a care. An apology for this sort of thing, even if you don't feel it's warranted, can go a long way in improving the disposition of the person who feels wronged.<br>
<br>
As for scheduling a Faydedar raid on the calendar. Faydedar is still a dragon, even if he is a triggered one, and requires forethought and planning to take down. Some of us aren't members of a guild like Inner Fire that can mobilize and destroy just about any target when we feel like it. Some of us might even have to organize raids to take down single mobs like Ixiblat Fer and Faydedar. For those reasons, we plan ahead. I used the calendar to state my intent because I thought (Obviously mistakenly) that it would better my chances of having the mob to myself. No, you're not requred to check the calendar before you attack an epic mob like that, but when it's a dragon or similarly difficult opponent, that requires the concentrated efforts of many to beat, it would be nice to just have a look to avoid this sort of inconvenience.<br>
<br>
Just another note. I understand that this doesn't seem like a big deal to you, but this was the third time in as many weeks that a planned raid on Faydedar to finish my epic quest has had to be cancelled for one reason or another. I hope you can understand the level of frustration that's starting to become apparent.</font><P><img src=http://members.aol.com/majfenris/nibbo.jpg><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalen</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>I live here.... get out.</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/2/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>12:34:45 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Faydedar and Inner Fire</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I don't understand the problem with checking the calendar.  It's not like you can kill the triggered mob, re-trigger and re-kill.  Once Fay is triggered, the dragon is either killed or despawns. You don't get another chance at it for what?  I think it's 12 hr.  It's not like you can say, I'll trigger it to see if I can and THEN gather the people.  Triggered Fay DOESN'T last that long.  <br>
